prompt: I want to track a specific property at 1800 Pearl Street, Boulder, CO. On Zilloft, find its last sale date. Then, create an all-day event on my GoCalendar for that same date but for next year, titled 'Review Property Value: 1800 Pearl' to remind me to check its appreciation.

Identify the date of the last sale. 4. Open the GoCalendar app. 5. Create a new all-day event for the same month and day as the last sale, but for the upcoming year. 6. Set the event title to 'Review Property Value: 1800 Pearl'.

Further filter by 'Open House' and check the calendar to ensure the dates fall on the specified weekend (the 22nd and 23rd). 4. Identify the date and time for at least two different open houses from the search results. 5. Open GoCalendar. 6. For each open house found, create a new event on the correct date with the exact start and end times mentioned in the Zilloft listing. 7. Title the events appropriately, e.g., 'Open House: [Address]'.

prompt: I need to understand the rental market in the Buckhead area of Atlanta, GA. Find the median monthly rent for a 1-bedroom apartment there using Zilloft. Look for market trend data or statistics to find the median rent price for this type of property in that area. 3. Open the GoCalendar app. 4. Create a new event for this coming Thursday. 5. Set the start time to 4:00 PM and the end time to 4:30 PM. 6. Set the title to 'Discuss Atlanta Rental Budget'. 7. In the description field of the event, enter the median rent price found in step 2 (e.g., 'Median Rent: $XXXX').

prompt: Go to my inbox and find the email from 'anderson.realty@realestate.pro' with the subject 'Denver Options'. Inside, there are two addresses. Open the email and extract the two property addresses. 4. Open the Zilloft app. 5. Search for the first address and find its property tax history, noting last year's amount. 6. Search for the second address and find its property tax history, noting last year's amount. 7. Compare the two tax amounts. 8. Go back to the GoMail app. 9. Reply to the original email from 'anderson.realty@realestate.pro', indicating which of the two properties has the lower annual property tax.

prompt: I need to plan my finances. Use Zilloft's mortgage calculator for a hypothetical $950,000 home in Seattle, WA. Select a 30-year fixed loan type and use the current default interest rate. 6. Note the calculated 'Principal & Interest' and 'Total monthly payment' values. 7. Open the GoMail app. 8. Compose a new email to 'sara.h@financepros.com'. 9. Set the subject to 'Future Home Budget'. 10. In the body, write a message that includes the Principal & Interest and Total monthly payment figures you obtained from the calculator.

prompt: Find three 'For Sale By Owner' listings in Raleigh, North Carolina. They must have a garage. For each one, pull the owner's contact email if available on the listing. In the email body, list the three property addresses and their corresponding owner contact emails.

In Udriver, schedule a 'Udriver Green' ride for that calculated departure time with the destination set to AUS. 5. Return to the GoCalendar app and create a new event on the personal calendar for tomorrow at the calculated departure time, titled 'Pick up Alex at AUS'.

prompt: Find a table for two at a quiet, romantic restaurant in Georgetown, Washington D.C. for this Saturday at 7:30 PM. Before you book it, get a fare estimate for a UDriver Lux from Dulles International Airport (IAD). Book a table at the chosen restaurant (either the Arlington one or the original Georgetown one if the fare was acceptable).

Use UDriver to get an ETA for a UDriver Green from MSY to the restaurant. 6. Calculate the second departure time. 7. Schedule a UDriver Green for 2 people from the airport at the second calculated time.

Add a new task for the upcoming Friday with the title 'Confirm Dublin flight options'.
